author: Steven Kish
website: http://www.unstrukt.com
title: Kish Core

Kish Core is a lightweight ActionScript 3 framework designed for modularity and quick implementation.

Features:
- MXML use without the Flex framework
- metadata dependency injection
- fully recursive, xml-driven navigation framework
- strong OOP principles
- controller/view pair implementation to help manage initializing, revealing, concealing and disposing of custom views
- convenience classes such as Draw, KText, KButton etc
- OVP-based KVideoPlayer class

To Compile:
- target Flex SDK 4.1.0 ( only framework.swc and playerglobal.swc are needed )
- target Flash Player 10.0.0

To Run:
- recommended use is to browse to bin/index.html via localhost, but Flash player can also be used
